App Privacy Policy
This information (hereinafter,
"Information"
or
"Cookie Policy"
) governs the processing of your personal data during the use of the application by
3BMeteo S.r.l.
with registered office at Via Don Carlo Botta 13, Bergamo (BG), Italy, VAT ID 04193510163, email support@3bmeteo.com (hereinafter, the "Data Controller"), in accordance with personal data protection regulations, particularly EU Regulation 2016/679 (hereinafter, "GDPR"), through the application you are using (hereinafter, the
App
).
1. Identity and contact details of the data controller
The Data Controller is
3B Meteo S.r.l.
As the Controller is established in Italy, no representative has been appointed.
2. Contact details of the data protection officer
The Data Controller has appointed a Data Protection Officer (
"DPO"
) pursuant to Article 37 of the GDPR. The DPO can be contacted at the following address:
dpo@3bmeteo.com
.
3. Processing methods
Paywall
The Data Controller's business model is based on the installation of tracking tools that involve profiling or, alternatively, on the acceptance of the
General Conditions of Use
to allow you to use the services provided through the App. Consequently, we offer you the following alternatives:
Easy Level:
without the installation of profiling tracking tools, in the absence of a subscription, you will be guaranteed very limited access to the service, coinciding with access to the information on the homepage and limited to one location per session;
Standard Level without profiling:
you can use the standard services offered through the App by subscribing at €6 per year, accepting the related
General Conditions of Use
. It is understood that in this case, you may still receive non-personalized advertisements;
Standard Level with profiling:
you can consent to the installation of profiling cookies, thus supporting the financing of the App. You can revoke your consent at any time, as specified in this Information.
3B+:
you can enjoy the standard services and additional services offered through the App by subscribing to 3B+ and accepting the related
General Conditions
.
We remind you that 3BMeteo does not operate on an exclusive basis. Should you not wish to subscribe and do not intend to accept profiling activities, you can enjoy the homepage of the website or choose one of the many alternative services.
At any time, you can refuse profiling activities and subscribe to a subscription and vice versa, also by accessing the privacy control panel within the App.
Identifiers and tracking tools
The App uses the following identifiers and tracking tools: Android Advertising ID and Apple IDFA, upon a new visit by you, allowing the collection of information about your browsing activity.
The described identifiers and tracking tools can be stored permanently on the App and have a variable duration, or they may not be persistently stored on your device and be automatically deleted upon closing the App.
The described identifiers and tracking tools can be installed by the App you are using or may be installed by third parties providing various services to such App (third parties).
3.1 Technical Identifiers and Tools
The identifiers and tracking tools in this category allow the App to function correctly and enable you to enjoy the "easy level" services on the App, in the case of no subscription and refusal to install profiling identifiers and tools.
3.2 Statistical Identifiers and Tools
The App also uses statistical identifiers and tracking tools made directly by the Data Controller or provided by third parties. With those made directly by the Data Controller, the latter will carry out statistical analyses related to the use of the App, proceeding with the statistical processing on their own, without such analyses being aimed at making commercial decisions. With those from third parties, tools have been adopted to reduce their identifying power, as the third party has contractually committed to the Data Controller to use them exclusively for the provision of the service, to keep them separately and not to "enrich" or "cross-reference" them with other information they have. Regarding identifiers and/or tracking tools from third parties, these may act as independent data controllers, in accordance with the conditions of use indicated.
Navigation Data and Environmental Variables
The App automatically acquires some personal data related to its use. This category of personal data includes, for example:
the IP addresses of the computer you used;
the number of accesses;
the pages used;
the date and time of access;
characteristics of the device used;
the operating system used.
3.3 Marketing Identifiers and Tools
Marketing identifiers and tracking tools allow the Data Controller to carry out marketing activities.
3.4 Profiling Identifiers and Tracking Tools
Profiling identifiers and tracking tools enable the Data Controller to tailor advertisements based on your preferences. The Data Controller uses those listed below.
